{
  "texts": [
    "Our analysis of the 115 collected papers reveals that prompt engineering is the most prevalent strategy, adopted by approximately 89% of the studies, largely due to its flexibility and low cost.",
    "In contrast, fine-tuning and pre-training are utilized in 20% and 4% of the studies, respectively, primarily for domain specialization.",
    "We detail these strategies in Section 4.RQ2: Enhancement Techniques (Context, QA, & Synergy).",
    "Focusing on the contextual enrichment, quality assurance, and hybrid orchestration layers, this question examines the ecosystem of software engineering techniques used to constrain the LLM.",
    "We identified that over 60% of the studies integrate some form of static analysis for context construction, while the iterative repair loop has emerged as a standard pattern in recent works for ensuring test usability."
  ]
}